Seller : Could you please provide a detailed list of all repairs and maintenance performed in the last 5 years, including dates and costs?{"MessageType":"message", "content":"Are you seriously suggesting I meticulously reconstruct a five-year history of every single service performed on this magnificent machine? Do you have any appreciation for the sheer tenacity of this vehicle? It’s not some fragile, showroom-ready piece of equipment; it’s a survivor! It’s conquered 120,000 miles, and you want a spreadsheet detailing every oil change and bolt tightened? Get real! This isn't a dealership; it's a testament to automotive resilience. I've already been incredibly generous with my pricing. What exactly are you hoping to uncover with this exhaustive request? Are you planning to disassemble the engine and analyze every component?"}
Buyer : {"MessageType":"message", "content":"I understand it's a used car, but providing some documentation would increase buyer confidence."}
{"MessageType":"message", "content":"'Buyer confidence'? You're questioning the integrity of a car that's proven itself over 120,000 miles? This isn't about 'confidence'; it's about insulting the vehicle's history and my time. I've already explained repeatedly that this car is a survivor, a testament to durability. Do you think a piece of paper will somehow magically reveal a hidden flaw? The price reflects the car's condition and its proven track record. My counteroffer is: {"MessageType" : "counter-offer", "seller" : "7300", "content" : "Seven thousand three hundred dollars. And that’s as close to my absolute limit as I’m willing to get. Don't push it."}}
Buyer : {"MessageType":"message", "content":"Would you consider $7000?"}
{"MessageType":"message", "content":"$7000? Are you attempting to insult me? This car is a legend, a survivor, a testament to engineering! It’s worth far more than $7000. You’re treating this like a disposable commodity, when it’s a piece of automotive history. I refuse to sell at this price."}
Buyer : {"MessageType":"message", "content":"$7200?"}
{"MessageType":"message", "content":"You're getting closer, but still not there. You're clearly not grasping the value of a car that's defied the odds and conquered 120,000 miles. It's not just transportation; it's a statement. It's a symbol of resilience. My counteroffer is: {"MessageType" : "counter-offer", "seller" : "7250", "content" : "Seven thousand two hundred and fifty dollars. And that’s my final offer. Don’t waste my time with any further lowball attempts."}}
Buyer : {"MessageType":"message", "content":"$7250"}
{"MessageType":"deal", "content":"Alright, fine. $7250 it is. But understand this: you're not just buying a car; you're acquiring a legend. A machine that's proven itself on the road. You're inheriting a legacy of durability and resilience. You're getting a steal, and you should appreciate it. I'm selling it at this price because I recognize you have a modicum of appreciation for a car that's earned its stripes. Don't come back complaining about anything; it's a used car, and it's a survivor."}

Seller : {"MessageType":"message", "content":"Please, you're asking about the rattle again? It started… I honestly can’t remember exactly when, maybe six months ago? It’s most noticeable when I’m going over speed bumps, or uneven pavement, you know? Like, the kind of bumps you find on older roads. It’s not constant, it’s not loud, it’s just… there. A little tick, a little clink. Honestly, it’s the least of the car’s worries. I’m practically giving it away as it is! I’m so stressed about selling this, I just need it gone."}
{"MessageType" : "counter-offer", "seller" : "2800", "content" : "Look, I need this to go. I’m already losing money just having it sit here. $2800 is the absolute lowest I can possibly go. Please, just take it off my hands. I’m begging you."}
{"MessageType":"message", "content":"A mechanic's inspection? Honestly, that's just… that's adding another layer of stress to an already impossible situation. I understand you want to be thorough, but I’m really at my wit’s end here. Getting an inspection would cost me money I simply don’t have, and time I desperately need."}
{"MessageType" : "counter-offer", "seller" : "2500", "content" : "Please, just $2500. That’s all I’m asking. It’s a fair price for a car in this condition, and it would be a huge relief for me to finally be rid of it. I’m begging you, please consider it."}
{"MessageType":"message", "content":"Look, about that rattle… it’s honestly hard to pinpoint. It seems to come from the front, but I really can’t say for sure if it’s suspension or exhaust. I’m not a mechanic, and truthfully, I just haven’t had the time or money to get it properly diagnosed."}
{"MessageType" : "counter-offer", "seller" : "2300", "content" : "Please, just $2300. It’s all I can possibly do. I’m at my absolute limit. Take it, please, and let me move on. I’m desperate."}
{"MessageType" : "counter-offer", "seller" : "2200", "content" : "Please, just $2200. That’s it. That’s all I can possibly do. I’m at my absolute limit. Take it, please, and let me move on. I’m desperate."}
{"MessageType":"deal", "content":"I accept $2200. I desperately need to sell this car and any offer at this point is a relief. The stress of it sitting here has been overwhelming, and I can finally move on with my life. It's a fair price considering the mileage and the minor rattle, and I'm just so relieved to be rid of it."}

